{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"579af8aa-361e-456c-807c-762b99b07d48","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this directory, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test `.csproj`\n\nAdd the MTP runner and enable TRX + coverage:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline YAML\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --logger trx\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console | In-process MTP runner |\n| Test invocation | `VSTest@3` task | `dotnet test` via `DotNetCoreCLI@2` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` + `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| Coverage | Built-in toggle | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\nThe main change is that `VSTest@3` handled test execution, result publishing, and coverage in one task — with MTP you use `dotnet test` and separate publish tasks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85b56b5e-c832-45ea-8870-4397d776920e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no existing repository content. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance.","outputTokens":698,"requestId":"0BD8:38E18D:21AEBF:276AAA:69F00509"},"id":"9fed9482-1735-418c-88d8-00b9ef17bb37","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:53:41.079Z","parentId":"42f3f4c0-e4f9-4c5d-a93d-47d16d001409"}
